  "body": "I am running about 35K pairs and using the abigen bindings for the Univ2Pair contract watchSwap and watchSync. The only thing I'm doing is launching one go routine for each and listening to the logs like this : \r\n\r\n```\r\nfunc (pairInstance *UniV2Pair) runSwapListener() {\r\n\r\n\tswapEvent := make(chan *v2pair.V2pairSwap)\r\n\r\n\t// Watch for Swap events\r\n\tsubscription, swapErr := pairInstance.Contract.WatchSwap(\r\n\t\tnil,\r\n\t\tswapEvent,\r\n\t\tnil,\r\n\t\tnil,\r\n\t)\r\n\tdefer subscription.Unsubscribe()\r\n\r\n\tif swapErr != nil {\r\n\t\tfmt.Println(swapErr)\r\n\t}\r\n\t// Loop to receive events\r\n\tfor {\r\n\t\tselect {\r\n\t\tcase <-swapEvent:\r\n\t\t\t//received a swap\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t}\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n![watchlogs](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/assets/3601695/fae06112-1e50-405f-99f9-aabbb826321b)\r\n\r\nDo you know if this is the correct behavior or I'm doing something wrong ? I assume that spawning the routines for 35K pairs is a lot, and the initial allocation should be high. But why does it keep on growing ? Thanks\r\n",
